abstract: “He has a Purple Heart and he has a Harvard degree,” Jimmy Fallon said of Lt. Col. Alexander S. Vindman. “Or as Trump put it, ‘Psh, who are you going to believe: him or me?’”

abstract: Trailing in the money race, tripped up by their own missteps and perceived by some as less electable, nonwhite candidates find themselves well back of the leaders.
snippet: Trailing in the money race, tripped up by their own missteps and perceived by some as less electable, nonwhite candidates find themselves well back of the leaders.
lead_paragraph: When the Democratic primary contest began last winter, it featured the most racially diverse field in history, with two black senators, a Latino former cabinet secretary, an Asian-American businessman and the first American Samoan elected to Congress. But 10 months later, the Democratic field has a top tier of four white candidates, three of them men.

abstract: J Street, a liberal pro-Israel advocacy group, hosted five of the Democratic presidential hopefuls at its meeting on Israel and the future of American foreign policy.
snippet: J Street, a liberal pro-Israel advocacy group, hosted five of the Democratic presidential hopefuls at its meeting on Israel and the future of American foreign policy.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Pete Buttigieg on Monday compared Israel’s relationship with the United States to that of a close friend — one who needed and should accept more guidance. Bernie Sanders put it in starker terms, saying the United States should demand more from Israel.

abstract: Every top Democrat is making calculations to try to win Iowa’s first-in-the-nation caucuses. But for Mr. Sanders, the political pressure and personal stakes are unique.
snippet: Every top Democrat is making calculations to try to win Iowa’s first-in-the-nation caucuses. But for Mr. Sanders, the political pressure and personal stakes are unique.
lead_paragraph: MARSHALLTOWN, Iowa — On a trip to Iowa in June, Senator Bernie Sanders confided in aides about a central gamble of his second bid for the White House.

abstract: The sixth debate, hosted by PBS NewsHour and Politico, will be held at U.C.L.A. on Dec. 19.
snippet: The sixth debate, hosted by PBS NewsHour and Politico, will be held at U.C.L.A. on Dec. 19.
lead_paragraph: The Democratic National Committee announced on Friday that the sixth Democratic primary debate would be held in December at the University of California, Los Angeles, while ratcheting up the polling and donor criteria for candidates to qualify for a coveted spot onstage.

abstract: Surveys released this week show varying, and sometimes conflicting, races unfolding nationally and in early primary states.
snippet: Surveys released this week show varying, and sometimes conflicting, races unfolding nationally and in early primary states.
lead_paragraph: Just over three months before Iowans caucus for Democratic presidential candidates, four polls out this week present a muddled picture of a primary race that is unfolding in varying, and sometimes conflicting, ways nationally and in early-voting states.
